Open storage availability at Thames Enterprise Park, Stanford-le-Hope, where the Landlord can offer up to 10 acres in a single plot. The site has now been cleared and there are various plot sizes available to let on flexible lease terms. 

The site is situated at the eastern end of The Manorway (A1014) on the north bank of the Thames Estuary, 11.6 miles east of the M25. The A1014 road is a dual carriageway and provides direct access to Junction 30 of the M25 via the A13 road.

Thames Enterprise Park is located immediately to the east of London Gateway which is a deep water container port that is being developed by DP World.

The site is situated at the extreme eastern end of The Manor Way (A1014). All but 2 miles of the A1014 is dual carriageway which provides access to the A13 and Junction 30 of the M25.

Boxset Basildon comprises three new speculative industrial warehouses located to the north east of Basildon Town Centre in a prominent position with direct access to A127.  

This Grade A warehouse is available for occupation immediately.

Boxset Basildon comprises a new 10 acre development site located to the north east of Basildon Town Centre in a prominent position with direct access to A127.  

This speculative build will be available from Q3 2019 offering prime industrial or warehouse opportunities. 

Central London within 45 minutes

Junction 29/M25 within 9 miles

Air and rail freight ports within 10 miles

Close to the sea ports of London Gateway, Tilbury and Felixstowe.

Velocity Harlow is a brand new industrial development in the heart of Harlow Business Park. The property located on Parkend, forming part of
Harlow Business Park and provides easy access to the A414, M11 and M25. Harlow Town Centre is located approximately two miles to the west of the property. Adjacent occupiers include, Brakes, Bidfood and Molecular.
